&lt;h1 id="made-in-usa"&gt;Made in USA&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;November 2004&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;(This is a new essay for the Japanese edition of Hackers &amp;amp; Painters. It tries to explain why Americans make some things well and others badly.)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A few years ago an Italian friend of mine travelled by train from Boston to Providence. She had only been in America for a couple weeks and hadn&amp;rsquo;t seen much of the country yet. She arrived looking astonished. &amp;ldquo;It&amp;rsquo;s so ugly!&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>